reviews.review: It was amazing and answered all my questions.

I'm a 1977 original Star Wars kid who waited around the block to watch the original trilogy movies. For me, this saved me from the horrible experience that The Last Jedi was. The Rise of Skywalker had a great balance of surprises mixed with nostalgia, all the while tying up loose ends and making sense of the previous installment's confusion and pandering. I consider what has been done in this movie brilliant.

Overall I liked it and will watch it when I marathon the other films.  My initial feeling for the movie was how it felt like a lot of it was remediation for The Last Jedi.  And it also felt like the Skywalker Saga was a term paper and The Rise of Skywalker had to cram as much information in to get it done.

There was alot of story to cover (and some  ugly holes to fill from the other movies) however, I thoroughly enjoyed this movie.  A good ending to an amazing franchise... if we could just delete Jar Jar from our memories!
it was mediocre, come from a hardcore SW fan
I really enjoyed this movie! It had all the elements of a fantastic Star Wars movie. Loved how they concluded the series. I will definitely be seeing this movie again.
Loved it. Thank you JJ for course correcting.  Three little words is all it took.
Great conclusion to the Skywalker story

Well it was well acted, decently shot, poorly written, difficult to follow, horribly in need of script editors, and it was sort of the branflakes of movies. There was nothing substantively interesting, it all just goes by and before you know it the movie is over. Where "The Last Jedi" was a slow, kind-of annoying movie, (though I did actually enjoy watching it, I understand it's not "technically good" I know it has some severe flaws, but over all, excluding the scenes with Rose, I thought it was fairly enjoyable. Also the actor for Rose was not bad, she did fine with what she was given) "Rise of Skywalker" is wildly fast but still unengaging film. 

However John Williams does an incredible job once again. and I can't help smiling at anything even remotely nostalgic. 

So I would say look into all the drama with George Lucas and Disney and keep it in mind while you're watching the movie, but also know that this movie had the burden of tying up a series that has existed since 1977 and for what the Last Jedi had done to J. J. Abrams original plan I think they did the best they could. Two and a half stars.
